    <description>The SOHO space telescope is an ESA Observatory that has been operating since 1996. The main body of the SOHO spacecraft is about 4.3m x 2.7m x 3.7m; the solar panels increase the width to about 9.5m when deployed. The spacecraft is in a halo orbit around the Sun-Earth L1 Lagrange point. Its science payload include 12 instruments contributed by various international collaborators.</description>
